description:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are you a level 1 registered nurse with a broad experience of community nursing?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you have an interest and specialist knowledge in infection prevention and control?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you want to join a progressive and innovative service in a social enterprise with a focus on staff development and positive patient outcomes?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you answered yes, we’ve got the perfect role for you!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for experienced and innovative community nurses with an interest in infection prevention and control to join our transformational service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will be responsible for IPC within a locality cluster: Strood/Rochester; Chatham/Lordswood or Rainham/Gillingham.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So what else?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will spend 2 days each week concentrating solely of the IPC element of the role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will need to be able to drive and have access to a vehicle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Our core hours are 7am to 7pm - but you will need to be flexible, working to the needs of our patients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We have full and part time hours available.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We encourage staff to get involved in exploring new ways of working and service development, with opportunities for CPD along the way.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This will be an evolving role; you will facilitate and eventually integrate into a neighbourhood nursing team with the aim of achieving 3 goals:&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing compassionate professional care of high quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health, wellbeing and fun at work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working in collaboration with the wider health and social care economy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So what are you waiting for? We can’t wait to hear from you, and look forward to receiving your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The small print&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Informal visits can be arranged on request.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We will offer you the choice of two pension schemes; the NHS Pension scheme and our Scottish Widows group personal pension.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If successfully shortlisted, you will be interviewed via video call no more than 14 days after this vacancy closes.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKaren CurtisJob titleLead CoachEmail addresskaren.curtis5@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
